The paper discusses the problem of generalized function matching, which is a topic in the field of combinatorial pattern matching. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions applications in computational biology, text editors, and data compression, which could also suggest that the paper belongs to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a heuristic algorithm and demonstrates its performance on human-produced text and random strings, which could suggest that the paper belongs to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
